Case Mr/Ms. Biroom vs. Mr. Medina - Tort action for trespassing
In legal terms, "Tort action for trespassing" refers to a lawsuit where someone sues another person for unlawfully entering their property without permission;
Mr. Medina braked into Ms. Biroom's house;
The lawyer of Mr. Medina alleged he was seeking shelter from the night. He thought the house was empty;
Mr. Medina was found guilty and sentenced to reimburse all damages caused to Mr. Biroom's house;
Mr. Medina will also need to perform community services.

IT It is one of the most used terms in the job market, yet the IT sector remains a difficult category to decipher. But what is IT, really? More than an Industry, it is a sector that cuts across every human activity known today, because it includes services and products to connect, communicate, process and share information and data.  Today the sector can no longer be reduced to just information technology and telecommunications. When we talk about IT and ICT (Information Technology and Information and Communication Technology) we talk about:

Information technologies, including software and operating systems for all devices and application development;
Telecommunications and infrastructures for network and telephone connections;
Internet connection for data exchange, with increasingly advanced systems such as the 5G network for a faster exchange of information or the creation of server farms for saving and sorting data;
Artificial intelligence and cloud computing, therefore the set of skills and technologies which, relying on ICT and IT infrastructures, automate processes that were once carried out manually.
The sectors that currently attract the most investments and have a strong innovative drive are above all artificial intelligence, machine learning and cloud computing, i.e. the ability to process data and information not on devices but on the network.

